WEBVTT

00:10.860 --> 00:12.060
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON "QUEEN SUGAR"...</i>

00:12.060 --> 00:13.390
Nova: MY FAMILY IS HAVING
TROUBLE WITH THE BOOK.

00:13.400 --> 00:14.460
I JUST NEED
SOME MORE TIME

00:14.460 --> 00:16.330
TO SMOOTH THINGS OUT
BEFORE THE BOOK TOUR.

00:16.330 --> 00:18.330
THIS STORY IS
GONNA HELP SO MANY PEOPLE --

00:18.330 --> 00:21.130
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
ABOUT SO MANY PEOPLE, NOVA!

00:21.130 --> 00:22.660
HE TRUSTS YOU.

00:22.660 --> 00:25.790
WHEN HE READS THIS,
HE'LL BELIEVE I'M A MONSTER.

00:25.800 --> 00:28.130
THIS BOOK AIN'T
JUST ABOUT EARNEST.

00:28.130 --> 00:30.130
"MY AUNT VIOLET,
BROKEN MORE TIMES

00:30.130 --> 00:31.330
THAN SHE CAN COUNT,

00:31.330 --> 00:33.330
BY MY UNCLE JIMMY DALE."

00:33.330 --> 00:34.930
NO, SHE DIDN'T.

00:34.930 --> 00:36.730
[ Voice breaking ]
YOU HAVE TO PUT
THE BRAKES ON IT.

00:36.730 --> 00:38.090
I CAN'T.

00:38.100 --> 00:40.030
IT'S GOING TO PRINT.

00:40.030 --> 00:42.390
[ LAMP CLICKS ]

00:42.400 --> 00:45.190
♪♪

00:45.200 --> 00:46.860
[ EXHALES DEEPER ]

00:46.860 --> 00:48.930
[ Quietly ]
GET IT TOGETHER, VI.

00:48.930 --> 00:52.060
♪♪

00:52.060 --> 00:53.390
[ SIGHS ]

00:53.400 --> 00:55.530
YOU ARE STRONGER THAN THIS.

00:55.530 --> 00:57.360
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR ]

00:57.360 --> 00:59.430
Hollywood: [ Muffled ]
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT IN THERE?

00:59.430 --> 01:01.390
FINE. I'LL BE OUT
IN A MINUTE.

01:01.400 --> 01:07.390
♪♪

01:07.400 --> 01:13.590
♪♪

01:13.600 --> 01:15.130
DON'T GIVE ME
THAT LOOK.

01:15.130 --> 01:17.190
WELL, YOU DON'T
SEEM FINE.

01:17.200 --> 01:19.290
AIN'T SEEMED
FINE ALL MORNING.

01:19.300 --> 01:22.090
IF I SAY I'M OKAY,
THEN I'M OKAY.

01:22.100 --> 01:23.890
WELL, WHAT YOU SAY
AND WHAT YOU ARE

01:23.900 --> 01:26.590
CAN BE TWO TOTALLY
DIFFERENT THINGS.

01:26.600 --> 01:28.730
NOW, BABY, I BEGGED YOU
DON'T STAY UP ALL NIGHT

01:28.730 --> 01:29.860
READING THAT BOOK.

01:29.860 --> 01:31.930
CALLED HER
THREE TIMES THIS MORNING.

01:31.930 --> 01:34.190
AH, SHE TOO SCARED TO ANSWER.
HELL, I WOULD BE, TOO.

01:34.200 --> 01:36.860
WELL, THEN SHE SHOULDN'T
HAVE PUT MY LIFE OUT THERE.

01:36.860 --> 01:39.590
FOR THE WORLD.

01:39.600 --> 01:42.530
I TOLD HER SHE BETTER
COME LOOK ME IN MY FACE

01:42.530 --> 01:43.860
BEFORE THE SUN
GOES DOWN

01:43.860 --> 01:45.530
BECAUSE I HAVE TO GO
TO THE 9th WARD

01:45.530 --> 01:46.890
LOOKING FOR HER,
I WILL.

01:48.560 --> 01:50.490
[ MAKEUP CLATTERS ]

01:50.500 --> 01:52.690
HOW COULD SHE DO THAT?

01:52.700 --> 01:57.590
♪♪

01:57.600 --> 01:58.990
HOW COULD SHE?

01:59.000 --> 02:01.560
♪♪

02:01.560 --> 02:03.760
Rhonda:
MORNING, MS. VI.

02:03.760 --> 02:04.890
MORNING, RHONDA.

02:04.900 --> 02:06.030
EVERYTHING
COPACETIC?

02:06.030 --> 02:07.290
OH, YES, MA'AM.

02:07.300 --> 02:10.630
OH, WE'RE RUNNING LOW
ON NAPKINS AND TO-GO CONTAINERS.

02:10.630 --> 02:12.730
CAN Y'ALL GRAB SOME
FROM THE BACK?

02:12.730 --> 02:13.890
GOT YOU, BABY.

02:13.900 --> 02:19.060
♪♪

02:19.060 --> 02:20.590
BABY, JUST GO ON
AND TAKE A SEAT

02:20.600 --> 02:22.130
AND I'LL BE
RIGHT WITH YOU.

02:22.130 --> 02:24.330
OF COURSE.

02:24.330 --> 02:25.390
THANK YOU.

02:25.400 --> 02:27.860
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS ]

02:27.860 --> 02:37.360
♪♪

02:37.360 --> 02:40.190
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU,
SWEETHEART.

02:40.200 --> 02:41.590
IT'S BEEN
A WHILE, HUH?

02:41.600 --> 02:48.860
♪♪

02:48.860 --> 02:55.990
♪♪

02:56.000 --> 02:57.590
IT'S BEEN
A WHILE.

