03:27.700 --> 03:28.630
♪ TAKE FLIGHT ♪

03:30.730 --> 03:32.260
-HERE YOU GO.
-VI? THANK YOU, BROTHER.

03:33.460 --> 03:35.460
COME ON. VI?

03:35.460 --> 03:36.660
I'LL GO GET
ANOTHER TOWEL.

03:36.660 --> 03:38.990
♪♪

03:39.000 --> 03:41.730
YOU OKAY, BABY?
YOU NEED A DOCTOR?

03:41.730 --> 03:43.460
Violet: WHAT HAPPENED?
YOU PASSED OUT.

03:43.460 --> 03:45.060
HERE, DRINK THIS.

03:45.060 --> 03:46.260
[ DOOR OPENS ]

03:49.130 --> 03:50.930
MM.

03:50.930 --> 03:52.930
WAIT.
WAIT, WHERE...

03:52.930 --> 03:56.390
♪♪

03:56.400 --> 03:58.790
WHAT HAPPENED?
-SHH, BABY, YOU OKAY, ALL RIGHT?

03:58.800 --> 04:00.460
YOU JUST GOT A LOT
ON YOUR MIND RIGHT NOW.

04:00.460 --> 04:02.930
THE OPENING HARVEST,

04:02.930 --> 04:04.260
NOVA,
AND ALL THAT STUFF.

04:04.260 --> 04:05.130
THAT'S IT, OKAY?

04:05.130 --> 04:06.590
BUT YOU GOT TO START
TAKING IT EASIER.

04:08.330 --> 04:10.990
HOLLYWOOD, UH,
LET'S, UH --

04:11.000 --> 04:12.860
LET'S GO HOME.

04:12.860 --> 04:14.360
I JUST NEED
A LITTLE REST, OKAY?

04:15.400 --> 04:17.460
OKAY.

04:17.460 --> 04:24.260
♪♪

04:24.260 --> 04:26.790
[ MUFFLED MUSIC
PLAYS FROM EARBUDS ]

04:26.800 --> 04:28.330
MICAH?

04:30.760 --> 04:39.360
♪♪

04:39.360 --> 04:48.260
♪♪

04:48.260 --> 04:56.930
♪♪

04:56.930 --> 04:59.190
MAYBE AFTER SCHOOL,

04:59.200 --> 05:01.190
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT
SOME OF THE THINGS

05:01.200 --> 05:03.260
THAT YOU'RE READING
IN THAT BOOK.

05:03.260 --> 05:05.960
I KNOW DAD DID
WHAT HE DID...

05:07.800 --> 05:08.890
...BUT...

05:10.000 --> 05:12.530
...YOU PAID MELINA GALOUDIAN
MILLIONS OF DOLLARS

05:12.530 --> 05:14.660
TO KEEP QUIET?

05:14.660 --> 05:16.460
I DID IT FOR YOU.

05:16.460 --> 05:19.330
FOR US.
FOR OUR PRIVACY.

05:19.330 --> 05:22.690
NOVA'S BOOK IS NOT HOW I WANTED
YOU TO LEARN ABOUT THAT.

05:26.600 --> 05:28.790
ALL I ASK IS THAT
YOU REMEMBER

05:28.800 --> 05:31.390
THAT WHAT'S BLACK AND WHITE
ON THE PAGES OF A BOOK

05:31.400 --> 05:35.460
IS OFTEN VERY...
GRAY IN -- IN REAL LIFE.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.660
PEOPLE SAY STUFF
LIKE THAT,

05:36.660 --> 05:38.190
BUT NEVER
WHAT THEY REALLY MEAN.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.990
I'M ON THE BOARD OF
LANDRY ENTERPRISES.

05:45.000 --> 05:46.790
YOU THINK IT'S BECAUSE
I WANT TO BE IN BUSINESS

05:46.800 --> 05:49.130
WITH THE FAMILY THAT
ENSLAVED OUR ANCESTORS?

05:49.130 --> 05:51.060
THAT I LOVE MONEY
THAT MUCH?

05:51.060 --> 05:53.190
OR IS IT BECAUSE
I NEED TO KNOW

05:53.200 --> 05:54.130
WHAT THEY'RE UP TO?

05:54.130 --> 05:55.660
I'M NOT
JUDGING YOU, MOM.

05:55.660 --> 05:57.660
I JUST DON'T...

05:57.660 --> 06:00.530
[SIGHS] UNDERSTAND YOU
SOMETIMES.

06:00.530 --> 06:02.360
SO, YOU BELIEVE
EVERYTHING YOU READ?

06:02.360 --> 06:03.430
NO.

06:06.660 --> 06:09.060
BUT THIS BOOK WAS WRITTEN
BY SOMEBODY I TRUST, SO...

06:10.130 --> 06:11.160
[ Quietly ]
"TRUST."

06:13.730 --> 06:15.160
WOW.

06:18.460 --> 06:19.860
SO YOU DON'T
TRUST ME?

06:19.860 --> 06:21.860
CAN WE TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE, PLEASE?

06:21.860 --> 06:30.190
♪♪

06:30.200 --> 06:33.260
[ LAPTOP CHIMING ]

06:33.260 --> 06:37.030
♪♪

06:37.030 --> 06:38.090
HEY, DEBORAH!

06:38.100 --> 06:39.230
PERFECT TIMING.

06:39.230 --> 06:40.460
I CAN'T DECIDE
WHAT OUTFIT TO WEAR

06:40.460 --> 06:42.130
FOR MY INTERVIEW
WITH DR. HALL.

06:42.130 --> 06:44.860
<i> I HEARD YOU SHOULD AVOID</i>
<i> RED, BLACK, AND WHITE</i>

06:44.860 --> 06:46.190
<i> WHILE ON CAMERA.</i>
GOOD TO KNOW.

06:46.200 --> 06:47.460
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ HANGERS RATTLE ]

06:47.460 --> 06:49.060
EVEN IF THE ONLY FOLKS
WHO ARE SEEING THIS

06:49.060 --> 06:50.660
ARE PSYCHOLOGY STUDENTS
OR THERAPY CENTERS,

06:50.660 --> 06:52.790
I, UH, WANT
TO PRESENT MYSELF RIGHT.

06:52.800 --> 06:54.860
<i> THAT MAY ALL BE</i>
<i> ABOUT TO CHANGE</i>

06:54.860 --> 06:55.990
<i> WITH THE NEWS</i>
<i> I'VE GOT FOR YOU.</i>

06:56.000 --> 06:58.330
<i> SO, WE GOT AN ADVANCE</i>

06:58.330 --> 07:00.090
<i> ON YOUR</i> NEW YORK TIMES
<i> BOOK REVIEW,</i>

07:00.100 --> 07:01.290
<i> AND, NOVA,</i>

07:01.300 --> 07:03.530
<i> IT'S A LOVE LETTER.</i>
A LOVE LETTER?

07:05.200 --> 07:06.630
FROM<i> THE TIMES?</i>

07:06.630 --> 07:07.960
WELL, WHEN DOES IT
COME OUT?

07:07.960 --> 07:10.090
<i> THIS AFTERNOON.</i>

07:10.100 --> 07:11.960
I WASN'T
EXPECTING THIS.

07:11.960 --> 07:13.260
<i> WELL, WE WERE.</i>

07:13.260 --> 07:14.590
<i> WE'VE BELIEVED IN YOU</i>
<i> FROM THE START.</i>

07:14.600 --> 07:16.460
THANK YOU.

07:16.460 --> 07:17.730
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

07:17.730 --> 07:18.860
<i> WELL, IT'S IN</i>
<i> YOUR INBOX,</i>

07:18.860 --> 07:21.590
<i> BUT HERE'S</i>
<i> AN APPETIZER.</i>

07:21.600 --> 07:24.930
<i> "'BLESSING AND BLOOD' IS</i>
<i> A NEAR-VIRTUOSO-LEVEL MEMOIR</i>

07:24.930 --> 07:27.530
<i> THAT SPEAKS IN BOTH</i>
<i> THE INTIMACY OF A WHISPER</i>

07:27.530 --> 07:30.790
<i> AND THE ROAR OF</i>
<i> AN URGENT CALL TO ACTION.</i>

07:30.800 --> 07:33.460
<i> NOVA BORDELON'S WRITING</i>
<i> FEELS AS IF IT'S FUELED</i>

07:33.460 --> 07:35.130
<i> BY BOTH FIRE</i>
<i> AND FEAR,</i>

07:35.130 --> 07:37.190
<i> A POTENT COMBINATION</i>
<i> THAT CATAPULTS</i>

07:37.200 --> 07:39.190
<i> THIS JOURNALIST-</i>
<i> TURNED-AUTHOR</i>

07:39.200 --> 07:42.330
<i> TO THE UPPER ECHELONS</i>
<i> OF WRITERS EXPLORING RACE,</i>

07:42.330 --> 07:45.260
<i> CULTURE, AND</i>
<i> IDENTITY IN AMERICA."</i>

07:45.260 --> 07:46.190
<i> I KNOW, RIGHT?</i>

07:47.630 --> 07:48.590
<i> ARE YOU THERE?</i>

07:50.360 --> 07:51.360
OH, MY GOD.

07:53.900 --> 07:56.060
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

07:56.060 --> 07:57.790
<i> YOUR WORK</i>
<i> SAYS IT ALL.</i>

07:57.800 --> 07:59.130
<i> IT'S MOVING NOW.</i>

07:59.130 --> 08:02.460
<i> IT'S CONNECTING WITH PEOPLE,</i>
<i> JUST LIKE YOU WANTED.</i>

08:02.460 --> 08:03.460
[ SIGHS ]

08:05.260 --> 08:07.130
GENERATOR READY
TO GO?

08:07.130 --> 08:09.460
ALTERNATOR'S
STILL BUSTED.

08:09.460 --> 08:11.730
MEANT TO CALL YOU
BEFORE YOU CAME.

08:11.730 --> 08:12.730
MY BAD.

08:12.730 --> 08:15.260
[ TRAIN HORN BLOWS ]

08:15.260 --> 08:17.230
TODAY JUST AIN'T
GOING MY WAY, MR. PROSPER.

08:19.700 --> 08:21.460
AH, YOU'RE DOING JUST FINE,
RALPH ANGEL.

08:21.460 --> 08:23.690
SO, WHAT'S ON
YOUR MIND?

08:26.000 --> 08:27.730
I DON'T KNOW.

08:27.730 --> 08:30.860
NOVA.
THE BOOK.

08:30.860 --> 08:32.930
SHE'S GOING IN
ON EVERYBODY.

08:32.930 --> 08:35.460
CHARLEY,
AUNT VI, BLUE.

08:35.460 --> 08:37.460
EVERYBODY?

08:37.460 --> 08:39.660
SOMETHING I NEED TO BE
CONCERNED WITH, TOO?

08:39.660 --> 08:41.460
I DOUBT IT.

08:41.460 --> 08:43.430
BUT KNOWING NOVA,
YOU NEVER KNOW.

08:43.430 --> 08:44.960
SO, WHAT DOES SHE GOT
TO WRITE ABOUT BLUE,

08:44.960 --> 08:47.930
OTHER THAN THE LOVE
SHE GOT FOR HIM?

08:47.930 --> 08:52.260
SHE TELLING THE WORLD
HE AIN'T MINE, PROSPER.

08:52.260 --> 08:55.130
THAT HE AIN'T
MY KID.

08:55.130 --> 08:56.860
'FORE HE EVEN KNOW.

08:56.860 --> 08:58.160
I SEE.

08:59.860 --> 09:01.090
YOU DON'T SEEM
SURPRISED.

09:02.860 --> 09:05.330
BY NOW,
I'VE LEARNED

09:05.330 --> 09:07.130
THAT LIFE
IS FULL OF SURPRISES.

09:07.130 --> 09:10.290
PLUS, I'VE SEEN
THIS KIND OF THING BEFORE.

09:13.600 --> 09:16.330
MY FATHER WASN'T
MY FATHER, EITHER.

09:16.330 --> 09:18.660
I MEAN, IF YOU MEAN IT
IN THE BIBLICAL WAY.

09:18.660 --> 09:20.760
FOR REAL?

09:20.760 --> 09:22.830
DIDN'T FIND OUT
TILL I WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,

09:22.830 --> 09:25.260
AND BY THEN,
I DIDN'T CARE.

09:25.260 --> 09:27.860
NOW, HE WAS GOOD TO ME.

09:27.860 --> 09:29.630
THAT'S THICKER
THAN BLOOD.

09:29.630 --> 09:31.390
SOUND LIKE
A GOOD MAN.

09:31.400 --> 09:32.390
YEP.

09:32.400 --> 09:34.590
HE WASN'T MY FATHER,
BUT HE WAS MY DADDY.

09:34.600 --> 09:36.660
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:36.660 --> 09:39.060
[ Sighing ]
YEAH.

09:39.060 --> 09:42.230
SO, THE WAY I LOOK AT IT
IS I WON.

09:42.230 --> 09:43.860
AND BLUE DID, TOO.

09:46.030 --> 09:48.030
A BOOK
DON'T CHANGE THAT.

09:48.030 --> 09:50.130
AND MAKE SURE
YOUR BOY KNOWS IT.

09:50.400 --> 09:51.460
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

09:51.460 --> 09:53.290
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

09:56.700 --> 09:57.960
OKAY, SLOW DOWN,
SLOW DOWN.

09:57.960 --> 09:59.130
SAY IT AGAIN.

09:59.130 --> 10:01.130
<i> IGNACIO.</i>
<i> ENFERMO.</i>

10:01.130 --> 10:02.230
UH, SICK.

10:02.230 --> 10:05.460
♪♪

10:08.930 --> 10:10.060
Host:
NOW, NOVA, WE'RE FORTUNATE
TO HAVE TWO FAMILIES

10:10.060 --> 10:12.190
THAT READ AN ADVANCE COPY
OF YOUR MEMOIR,

10:12.200 --> 10:14.130
AND THEY'RE HERE TO SHARE
THEIR EXPERIENCES

10:14.130 --> 10:16.130
AFTER READING
YOUR BOOK.

10:16.130 --> 10:17.530
Woman:
FOR A LONG TIME,

10:17.530 --> 10:20.430
MY MOTHER AND I REFUSED
TO ADDRESS OUR ISSUES.

10:23.330 --> 10:26.460
KIND OF LIKE YOU
AND CHARLEY.

10:26.460 --> 10:27.860
CAN I ASK
HOW YOU WERE ABLE

10:27.860 --> 10:30.130
TO BREAK THROUGH
ALL THE HURT FEELINGS

10:30.130 --> 10:32.830
AND THE TRAUMA TO GET
TO A HEALTHIER PLACE WITH HER?

10:32.830 --> 10:34.960
♪♪

10:34.960 --> 10:37.290
I FINALLY HAD TO LET GO
OF THE FEAR THAT STOPPED ME

10:37.300 --> 10:39.290
FROM THINKING ABOUT ANYTHING
IN MY RELATIONSHIPS

10:39.300 --> 10:42.660
THAT SADDENED ME,
LET ALONE ALONE DEAL WITH THEM.

10:42.660 --> 10:45.390
I REALIZED I WAS
SUPPRESSING EVERYTHING.

10:45.400 --> 10:47.260
BUT THAT'S JUST
PUTTING IT IN A DRAWER.

10:47.260 --> 10:49.730
IT'S NOT GONE.
IT'S JUST...

10:49.730 --> 10:51.460
AWAY.

10:51.460 --> 10:55.390
AND SOME DAY, SOMEBODY'S GOING
TO OPEN THAT DRAWER,

10:55.400 --> 10:57.160
AND THE PAIN
WILL STILL BE THERE.

10:57.160 --> 10:59.690
SO, I DECIDED
TO CLEAN OUT THE DRAWER

10:59.700 --> 11:02.060
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

11:02.060 --> 11:05.330
WRITING THIS WAS THERAPEUTIC
IN THAT WAY.

11:05.330 --> 11:06.590
AND IT'S AN EXPERIENCE

11:06.600 --> 11:09.330
I HOPE THOSE WHO READ IT
WILL HAVE, AS WELL.

11:09.330 --> 11:13.130
[ CELLPHONE DIALING ]

11:13.130 --> 11:14.730
Man:
<i> FRANCES BOUDREAUX'S OFFICE.</i>

11:14.730 --> 11:16.260
HI, THIS IS
CHARLEY BORDELON.

11:16.260 --> 11:17.860
<i> MS. BORDELON,</i>
<i> MRS. BOUDREAUX IS NOT</i>

11:17.860 --> 11:18.990
<i> TAKING CALLS</i>
<i> AT THIS TIME.</i>

11:19.000 --> 11:20.630
<i> CARE TO LEAVE</i>
<i> A MESSAGE?</i>

11:20.630 --> 11:25.760
♪♪

11:25.760 --> 11:27.360
YES.

11:27.360 --> 11:29.930
MY MESSAGE IS THAT I WANT
TO KNOW HOW JACOB BOUDREAUX

11:29.930 --> 11:33.860
GETS TO ATTEND BOARD MEETINGS
AND I DON'T.

11:33.860 --> 11:35.860
ESPECIALLY SINCE WE HAVE
THE SAME AMOUNT OF SHARES

11:35.860 --> 11:38.790
IN LANDRY ENTERPRISES.

11:38.800 --> 11:42.190
TELL FRANCES
I EXPECT A CALL BACK.

11:42.200 --> 11:44.760
SOON.

11:44.760 --> 11:46.560
[ SIGHS ]

11:50.430 --> 11:51.930
[ LID CLOSES, TOILET FLUSHES ]

11:53.230 --> 11:54.730
WHAT'S GOING ON, VI?

12:01.660 --> 12:05.460
BABY, YOU AIN'T SAY A WORD
ON THE WAY HOME,

12:05.460 --> 12:06.860
AND YOU DON'T WANT
NOTHING TO EAT.

12:09.660 --> 12:11.130
I'M SCARED FOR YOU.

12:13.330 --> 12:15.790
I SAW JIMMY DALE
AT THE DINER.

12:15.800 --> 12:17.630
SAW WHO?

12:17.630 --> 12:19.860
BALD-HEAD GUY

12:19.860 --> 12:22.790
WITH THE WHITE BEARD.

12:22.800 --> 12:24.330
OLD BOY WITH
A YELLOW SHIRT?

12:24.330 --> 12:29.930
♪♪

12:29.930 --> 12:31.530
SAID HE CAUGHT YOU
WHEN YOU PASSED OUT.

12:31.530 --> 12:37.790
♪♪

12:37.800 --> 12:40.130
HE PUT
HIS HANDS ON YOU?

12:40.130 --> 12:41.460
AND HE AIN'T EVEN SAY

12:41.460 --> 12:42.790
WHO HE WAS?
HOLLYWOOD --

12:42.800 --> 12:44.460
TRYING TO PLAY
THE GOOD SAMARITAN AND SHIT,

12:44.460 --> 12:45.930
HE GONNA TIP ON OUT
THE FRONT DOOR?

12:45.930 --> 12:46.860
OH, HELL NO!

12:49.000 --> 12:51.330
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

12:51.330 --> 12:53.390
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

12:53.400 --> 12:55.490
WHEN I REALIZED
IT WAS HIM,

12:55.500 --> 12:57.090
SOMETHING JUST HAPPENED.
[ CELLPHONE DIALING ]

12:59.430 --> 13:01.190
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?
HEY, RHONDA, THIS IS WOOD.

13:01.200 --> 13:02.190
Rhonda:
<i> HEY, HOLLYWOOD.</i>

13:02.200 --> 13:03.660
HEY, YOU REMEMBER
THAT CUSTOMER?

13:03.660 --> 13:04.990
<i> WHICH ONE?</i>

13:05.000 --> 13:06.790
YEAH, THE NEW GUY
WITH THE YELLOW SHIRT.

13:06.800 --> 13:08.990
<i> OH, YEAH?</i>

13:09.000 --> 13:10.660
LET ME KNOW
IF HE COME BACK IN.

13:11.730 --> 13:13.860
ALL RIGHT.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

13:13.860 --> 13:16.460
HOLLYWOOD, I DON'T WANT YOU TO
GET MIXED UP WITH HIS NONSENSE.

13:16.460 --> 13:17.860
HE'S GOOD AT THAT.

13:17.860 --> 13:21.130
OH, BABY,
ST. JOE'S AIN'T BUT SO BIG.

13:21.130 --> 13:23.190
HE AROUND HERE
SOMEWHERE.

13:23.200 --> 13:24.860
WORST THING IN YOUR LIFE

13:24.860 --> 13:27.290
COMING TO YOUR NEW PLACE
OF BUSINESS AFTER 30 YEARS?

13:29.660 --> 13:31.460
NAH, HE HERE
TO GET SOMETHING STARTED.

13:33.860 --> 13:35.390
BUT I'M-A FINISH IT.

13:36.260 --> 13:39.860
[ CELLPHONE RINGING, VIBRATING ]

13:39.860 --> 13:41.130
HEY, RALPH.

13:41.130 --> 13:42.090
SAY, I GOT
A LITTLE SITUATION

13:42.100 --> 13:44.090
OVER HERE
AT THE FARM.

13:44.100 --> 13:46.030
MIGHT MAKE ME LATE
TO MY OFFICE SLOT THIS WEEK.

13:46.030 --> 13:47.730
<i> THAT'S GONNA</i>
<i> BACK ME UP.</i>

13:47.730 --> 13:49.130
<i> YEAH, WELL,</i>
<i> I GOT CIRCUMSTANCES.</i>

13:49.130 --> 13:50.860
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

13:50.860 --> 13:52.790
IGNACIO.

13:52.800 --> 13:55.290
MY TOP WORKER,
HE GOT SICK.

13:55.300 --> 13:59.360
CAN'T GO TO A HOSPITAL,
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

13:59.360 --> 14:01.560
I MAY ACTUALLY KNOW
SOMEONE WHO CAN, UH --

14:01.560 --> 14:04.360
WHO CAN HELP WITH THAT.

14:04.360 --> 14:06.530
LET ME
CALL YOU BACK.

14:06.530 --> 14:08.130
KEKE.

14:08.130 --> 14:10.660
♪♪

14:10.660 --> 14:13.390
CAN WE TALK?

14:13.400 --> 14:14.430
I'M-A CATCH YOU LATER.
ALL RIGHT.

14:17.060 --> 14:18.190
I DON'T KNOW.
CAN WE?

14:18.200 --> 14:19.330
I'VE BEEN
TRYING TO.

14:19.330 --> 14:22.390
YOU HAVEN'T ANSWERED
ANY OF MY TEXTS.

14:22.400 --> 14:23.390
WE'RE AT
THE SAME SCHOOL.

14:23.400 --> 14:25.060
WE HAVE TO TALK
AT SOME POINT.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.290
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S TALK.

14:29.300 --> 14:31.330
WHY ARE YOU ACTING
ALL BRAND-NEW ON ME, HUH?

14:31.330 --> 14:32.860
FIGHTING A GUY
LIKE YOU SOME NEW-AGE THUG?

14:32.860 --> 14:33.930
YOU THINK
THAT'S CUTE?

14:33.930 --> 14:35.530
YOU KNOW HE HAD IT
COMING TO HIM.

14:35.530 --> 14:37.460
IF IT WASN'T ME, IT WAS
GOING TO BE SOMEONE ELSE.

14:37.460 --> 14:39.190
I'M NOT WITH
SOMEONE ELSE.

14:39.200 --> 14:40.760
I'M WITH
MICAH WEST.

14:40.760 --> 14:43.360
YOU --
YOU'RE RIGHT.

14:43.360 --> 14:45.290
OKAY?
IT WAS STUPID OF ME.

14:45.300 --> 14:47.830
I NEED TO BE MORE WISE
ABOUT THINGS.

14:47.830 --> 14:49.960
YOU'RE IMPORTANT
TO ME.

14:49.960 --> 14:52.090
WHAT YOU THINK ABOUT ME
IS IMPORTANT TO ME.

14:55.660 --> 14:59.330
JUST PROMISE ME THAT
IT WON'T GET THERE AGAIN?

14:59.330 --> 15:01.630
YOU NEED CHANNEL THAT ANGER
SOME OTHER WAY.

15:01.630 --> 15:03.560
I KNOW.
I'M WORKING ON IT.

15:03.560 --> 15:05.290
I CAN'T SAY
I WON'T DISAPPOINT YOU.

15:05.300 --> 15:07.460
I'M NOT PERFECT,
BUT...

15:10.630 --> 15:12.790
...I CAN PROMISE YOU
I WILL NEVER DISRESPECT YOU.

15:14.600 --> 15:15.730
MAMA TAUGHT ME
BETTER THAN THAT.

15:15.730 --> 15:21.130
♪♪

15:21.130 --> 15:23.060
WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON, JACOB?

15:26.360 --> 15:29.230
COULD YOU GIVE US
A MOMENT, HANK?

15:29.230 --> 15:31.290
MS. BORDELON.

15:31.300 --> 15:32.890
I'LL WAIT
JUST OUTSIDE.

15:32.900 --> 15:37.790
♪♪

15:37.800 --> 15:39.590
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

15:39.600 --> 15:40.730
WHO'S HE?

15:40.730 --> 15:43.390
AND HOW DOES HE
KNOW MY NAME?

15:43.400 --> 15:45.060
ONE -- YOU'RE KIND OF
FAMOUS,

15:45.060 --> 15:47.460
SO LOTS OF PEOPLE
KNOW YOUR NAME.

15:47.460 --> 15:49.590
AND TWO --
HE'S A NEW CONSULTANT.

15:49.600 --> 15:50.790
HANK MILLER.

15:50.800 --> 15:52.790
WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE CONSULTANTS?

15:52.800 --> 15:54.330
MARK KRYGER,
HANK MILLER --

15:54.330 --> 15:57.990
BUSINESSES HIRE
CONSULTANTS, CHARLEY.

15:58.000 --> 16:01.560
IT'S THEIR JOB TO KNOW
ALL OUR PRIMARY SHAREHOLDERS.

16:01.560 --> 16:04.030
WELL, I'M NOT EXACTLY
PRIMARY ANYMORE,

16:04.030 --> 16:06.030
AND NEITHER ARE YOU.

16:06.030 --> 16:07.890
YET YOU'RE ABLE
TO ATTEND BOARD MEETINGS

16:07.900 --> 16:10.760
WITHOUT POSSESSION OF
THE PROPER NUMBER OF SHARES...

16:10.760 --> 16:14.830
SAM COMBINED HIS SHARES
AND VOTING POWER WITH ME.

16:14.830 --> 16:18.060
HE PASSED NEW BYLAWS
SO FAMILY MEMBERS CAN ATTEND,

16:18.060 --> 16:19.760
EVEN IF WE DON'T
HAVE ENOUGH SHARES.

16:21.530 --> 16:24.230
AND TO THINK I GAVE YOU
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT

16:24.230 --> 16:26.360
THAT YOU GAINED
AN OUNCE OF DIGNITY.

16:26.360 --> 16:28.630
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

16:28.630 --> 16:30.630
[ OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS ]

16:30.630 --> 16:38.060
♪♪

16:38.060 --> 16:45.490
♪♪

16:45.500 --> 16:47.630
WHAT'S THIS
ALL ABOUT, JACOB?

16:47.630 --> 16:49.990
Jacob: YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
I LIKE YOU, CHARLEY.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.190
I NEED
TO LET YOU KNOW.

16:52.200 --> 16:54.930
I THINK IT'S BEST IF YOU DON'T
RUFFLE ANYMORE FEATHERS.

16:54.930 --> 16:56.860
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:56.860 --> 16:58.990
I DON'T RESPOND
TO THREATS.

16:59.000 --> 17:00.430
YOU KNOW WHAT MY FAMILY
IS CAPABLE OF.

17:02.730 --> 17:04.860
THEY'RE LIKE
A FREIGHT TRAIN.

17:04.860 --> 17:07.930
THEY STOP AT NOTHING
IN THEIR WAY.

17:07.930 --> 17:09.660
AND YOU SHUTTING DOWN
THE PRISON,

17:09.660 --> 17:11.730
IT DIDN'T EXACTLY
SLOW THINGS DOWN.

17:14.930 --> 17:17.190
THAT'S ALL
I'M AT LIBERTY TO SAY.

17:17.200 --> 17:19.530
SO NOW I'M SUPPOSED
TO TRUST

17:19.530 --> 17:21.790
THAT YOU CARE
ABOUT ME?

17:21.800 --> 17:24.660
MY FAMILY?

17:24.660 --> 17:26.190
WHERE'S YOUR MAMA?

17:26.200 --> 17:27.590
SHE CLAIMED
TO HAVE MY BACK,

17:27.600 --> 17:29.160
BUT NOW SHE'S NOWHERE
TO BE FOUND.

17:29.160 --> 17:32.230
SHE'S IN DC TAKING MEETINGS
TO EXPAND LANDRY ENTERPRISES.

17:32.230 --> 17:33.290
EXPANDING TO DO WHAT?

17:33.300 --> 17:35.390
THAT'S ALL
I KNOW RIGHT NOW.

17:35.400 --> 17:37.060
OH, THAT'S<i> ALL</i> YOU KNOW?

17:37.060 --> 17:39.590
♪♪

17:39.600 --> 17:42.590
SO, YOU'RE GONNA MAKE ME
WORK TO FIND OUT?

17:42.600 --> 17:43.960
FINE.

17:43.960 --> 17:45.960
I ACTUALLY KNOW
HOW TO WORK.

17:45.960 --> 17:48.660
THAT'S WHAT
YOU THINK OF ME?

17:48.660 --> 17:51.530
I'VE JUST BEEN HIGH ON THE HOG
SINCE BIRTH.

17:51.530 --> 17:53.190
SILVER SPOON
IN MY MOUTH,

17:53.200 --> 17:54.260
NEVER WORKED
FOR NOTHING.

17:54.260 --> 17:55.860
THAT'S WHAT YOU THINK?

17:55.860 --> 17:58.530
♪♪

17:58.530 --> 18:01.930
YOU'VE<i> HAD</i> A FAMILY.

18:01.930 --> 18:03.330
LOVE.

18:03.330 --> 18:04.730
CAMARADERIE.

18:04.730 --> 18:07.190
I NEVER HAD THAT.

18:07.200 --> 18:08.930
TO GET ANYTHING
CLOSE TO LOVE WITH US,

18:08.930 --> 18:10.590
YOU GOT
TO BREAK SKIN,

18:10.600 --> 18:13.730
SHOW BLOOD,
AND BE HAPPY ABOUT IT.

18:13.730 --> 18:15.060
I WAS NEVER
WIRED FOR IT.

18:15.060 --> 18:17.390
I ALWAYS HOPED
YOU'D SEE THAT.

18:17.400 --> 18:18.390
I STILL DO.

18:20.030 --> 18:24.330
THERE ARE THINGS GOING ON
THAT SHOULDN'T BE, CHARLEY.

18:24.330 --> 18:26.860
I'M TRYING
TO LOOK OUT FOR YOU.

18:26.860 --> 18:30.260
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST SIT BACK
AND ENJOY YOUR DIVIDENDS?

18:30.260 --> 18:32.460
FOR THE SAME REASON
YOU CAN JUST SIT BACK

18:32.460 --> 18:35.230
AND ENJOY
YOUR PRIVILEGE, JACOB.

18:35.230 --> 18:37.460
AT SOME POINT, WE ALL
MAKE OUR OWN CHOICES.

18:37.460 --> 18:39.130
YOUR FAMILY
MADE THEIRS,

18:39.130 --> 18:41.130
AND YOU'VE CHOSEN
TO GO ALONG.

18:42.130 --> 18:45.060
YOU TELLING A SAD STORY
ABOUT IT DOESN'T CHANGE IT.

18:45.060 --> 18:54.060
♪♪

18:54.060 --> 18:55.990
Hollywood: COFFEE HOT ENOUGH
FOR YOU?

18:56.000 --> 18:58.390
WELL, IT SURE IS.

18:58.400 --> 19:00.330
NOW, YOU MUST BE
THE MANAGER.

19:00.330 --> 19:02.860
I DIDN'T GET TO MEET YOU
EARLIER, PROPER LIKE,

19:02.860 --> 19:04.390
WHAT WITH
ALL THE COMMOTION.

19:04.400 --> 19:07.590
I SURE DO HOPE
VIOLET'S DOING OKAY.

19:07.600 --> 19:09.330
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE,

19:09.330 --> 19:10.960
JIMMY DALE,

19:10.960 --> 19:12.860
AND I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE ALL ABOUT,

19:12.860 --> 19:15.330
SO YOU CAN SAVE
"THE SHOWTIME AND THE APOLLO,"

19:15.330 --> 19:18.790
SKINNING AND GRINNING,
'CAUSE I KNOW WHAT'S BEHIND IT.

19:18.800 --> 19:21.430
SO DOES MY WIFE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:21.430 --> 19:22.960
OH, I SEE
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

19:22.960 --> 19:24.390
BUT YOU GOT THIS
ALL WRONG.

19:24.400 --> 19:27.190
SEE,
ME AND VIOLET,

19:27.200 --> 19:29.130
THINGS JUST DIDN'T WORK OUT.
THAT'S ALL.

19:29.130 --> 19:32.360
BUT THAT'S OLD WATER
UNDER AN OLD BRIDGE, MY FRIEND.

19:32.360 --> 19:34.490
I AIN'T YOUR FRIEND.

19:34.500 --> 19:37.260
I'M HOLLYWOOD DESONIER.

19:37.260 --> 19:38.730
AND I'M-A TELL YOU THIS
ONE TIME

19:38.730 --> 19:40.860
AND BE NOBLE ABOUT IT.

19:40.860 --> 19:43.090
YOU NEED TO BOUNCE.

19:44.600 --> 19:45.730
EXCUSE ME,
YOUNG BLOOD?

19:45.730 --> 19:47.590
SHE DON'T WANT YOU
AROUND HERE,

19:47.600 --> 19:48.660
AND NEITHER DO I.

19:48.660 --> 19:50.590
SO GO AHEAD
AND RAISE ON UP.

19:50.660 --> 19:54.130
[ LAUGHS ]

19:54.130 --> 19:55.460
AH-HA, HELL.

19:55.460 --> 19:56.660
YOU REMEMBER
EARNEST BORDELON?

19:58.460 --> 20:00.030
YEAH, EARNEST.

20:01.660 --> 20:04.060
SO, IF YOU WANT TO PAR TO
WITH THAT ASS-WHIPPING,

20:04.060 --> 20:06.730
THINK I'M PLAYING
WITH YOU.

20:06.730 --> 20:08.860
SO, GO AHEAD
AND PAY YOUR TAB,

20:08.860 --> 20:10.490
GET YOUR LITTLE GOOFY ASS
IN THE CAR,

20:10.500 --> 20:13.630
AND GET THE HELL UP OUT OF TOWN
BEFORE YOU CATCH THESE HANDS.

20:13.630 --> 20:15.990
♪♪

20:16.000 --> 20:19.060
WELL, I DON'T STAY
WHERE I'M NOT WANTED.

20:19.060 --> 20:20.330
I MEAN, I WAS JUST
DRIVING THROUGH.

20:20.330 --> 20:22.860
I JUST WANTED
TO WISH VIOLET GOOD LUCK

20:22.860 --> 20:24.530
WITH HER LITTLE DINER.
THAT'S ALL.

20:24.530 --> 20:28.530
I DON'T WANT NO TROUBLE.
DIDN'T MEAN NO DISRESPECT.

20:28.530 --> 20:31.190
YEAH.

20:31.200 --> 20:32.860
BUT, UH...

20:32.860 --> 20:37.330
THE BORDELONS WAS MY FAMILY TOO
FOR A LONG TIME.

20:37.330 --> 20:40.660
BUT THAT TIME DONE PASSED,
BUT THE PAST DON'T CHANGE.

20:40.660 --> 20:48.260
♪♪

20:50.260 --> 20:56.560
♪♪

20:56.560 --> 20:58.890
I DIDN'T GET
INTO IT WITH HIM, BABY.

20:58.900 --> 21:00.390
DIDN'T HAVE TO.
HE GONE.

21:00.400 --> 21:02.590
♪♪

21:02.600 --> 21:03.930
WELL, HOW'D YOU
MANAGE THAT?

21:03.930 --> 21:06.460
'CAUSE JIMMY
DON'T BACK DOWN EASY.

21:06.460 --> 21:08.930
MAYBE HE GETTING WISE
IN HIS OLD AGE,

21:08.930 --> 21:10.530
BUT I FOLLOWED HIS ASS
ALL THE WAY TO THE END

21:10.530 --> 21:12.130
OF ST. JO'S
PARISH LINE,

21:12.130 --> 21:15.590
WATCHED HIM HOP ON
THE FREEWAY HEADED WEST.

21:15.600 --> 21:17.530
AND ALL YOU DID
WAS TALK.

21:17.530 --> 21:18.830
THAT'S ALL.

21:18.830 --> 21:21.430
BUT HE WAS GETTING UP OUT OF
HERE COME HOOK OR BY CROOK.

21:21.430 --> 21:25.460
♪♪

21:25.460 --> 21:28.060
Ralph Angel: YEAH, I NEVER
TAKE NO REAL LUNCH BREAK,

21:28.060 --> 21:29.930
ESPECIALLY NOT LATE
LIKE THIS.

21:29.930 --> 21:32.860
I COULD
GET USED TO IT.

21:32.860 --> 21:34.860
THE ONE THING ABOUT WORKING
IN THE BUREAUCRACY

21:34.860 --> 21:37.130
OF THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT
I DON'T MIND...

21:37.130 --> 21:38.860
HM?
...IS PEOPLE CLOCK IN,

21:38.860 --> 21:41.590
TAKE THEIR BREAKS,
AND CLOCK THE HELL OUT.

21:42.660 --> 21:44.790
WHILE WE WAS ON THE PHONE
THE OTHER NIGHT,

21:44.800 --> 21:46.790
SAID YOU WAS WORKING
FROM HOME, RIGHT?

21:46.800 --> 21:49.330
I'M NEVER GONNA
LET MY CASES SUFFER,

21:49.330 --> 21:51.090
BUT I AM GONNA
EAT MY DAMN LUNCH, TOO.

21:51.100 --> 21:53.430
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

21:53.430 --> 21:54.790
MMM.

21:54.800 --> 21:58.330
I, UM --
I KNOW IT'S HARVEST TIME.

21:58.330 --> 22:01.390
I DIDN'T --
I DIDN'T THINK YOU'D MAKE IT.

22:01.400 --> 22:03.460
NEEDED A LITTLE BREAK.
MM.

22:03.460 --> 22:06.460
WORKING AROUND THE CLOCK,
YOU KNOW?

22:06.460 --> 22:08.730
BESIDES...

22:08.730 --> 22:10.190
I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

22:10.200 --> 22:13.060
♪♪

22:13.060 --> 22:15.060
Charley:
VICKY, I NEED YOU TO LOOK
INTO SOMETHING FOR ME.

22:15.060 --> 22:17.590
I-I RECEIVED THE MINUTES
FROM THE BOARD MEETING,

22:17.600 --> 22:23.060
AND I SAW A $1.5 MILLION
PURCHASE OF UNIDENTIFIED LAND,

22:23.060 --> 22:26.860
ODDLY TUCKED UNDER
"OPERATIONAL EXPENDITURES,"

22:26.860 --> 22:29.260
AND I HAVE NO CLUE
WHAT THAT'S FOR.

22:29.260 --> 22:31.460
YEAH, I'M JUST TRYING TO --
TRYING TO GET UP TO SPEED.

22:31.460 --> 22:33.390
UM...

22:33.400 --> 22:35.860
COULD YOU LOOK INTO IT
IF I E-MAILED IT FOR YOU?

22:35.860 --> 22:38.660
YEAH.
YEAH, OKAY.

22:38.660 --> 22:39.990
THANKS, VICKY.

22:40.000 --> 22:40.990
YOU'RE THE BEST.

22:43.200 --> 22:45.090
HI.

22:45.100 --> 22:46.960
WOW.

22:46.960 --> 22:48.030
THANK YOU.

22:48.030 --> 22:50.360
THIS IS SO...
ON TIME.

22:50.360 --> 22:54.990
♪♪

22:55.000 --> 22:56.930
YOU ARE VERY WELCOME.

22:56.930 --> 23:00.590
IT'S GOOD TO BREAK UP THE WORK
DAY EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE, YEAH?

23:00.600 --> 23:02.090
YEAH, IT IS.

23:04.230 --> 23:05.960
AND YOU'LL BE PLEASED TO KNOW
THAT YOUR BROTHER'S WORK HERE

23:05.960 --> 23:07.530
WILL BE FINE.

23:07.530 --> 23:09.460
GLAD YOU CALLED ME.
[ SIGHS ]

23:09.460 --> 23:11.930
THANKS FOR
MAKING THE TIME.

23:11.930 --> 23:15.130
YEAH, YOUR BROTHER'S, UH,
DOING GOOD BY HIS MEN,

23:15.130 --> 23:16.930
TAKING GOOD CARE
OF THEM.

23:16.930 --> 23:18.060
THAT'S NICE TO SEE.

23:18.060 --> 23:19.390
YOU DON'T SEE THAT
VERY OFTEN.

23:19.400 --> 23:20.330
HM.

23:20.330 --> 23:22.790
SOME OF THE THINGS
I'VE HEARD...

23:22.800 --> 23:24.660
I'VE SEEN SOME, UH,
PRETTY MESSED UP STUFF

23:24.660 --> 23:26.930
IN ST. JO THAT
YOU WOULDN'T EXPECT.

23:26.930 --> 23:28.130
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

23:28.130 --> 23:32.290
STUFF THAT, UH,
JUST STAYS WITH YOU.

23:32.300 --> 23:35.230
LIKE, UM,
THOSE TWO MIGRANT WORKERS,

23:35.230 --> 23:36.930
THE ONES THAT
WERE, UH, KILLED

23:36.930 --> 23:40.730
ON ONE OF THE FARMS
A FEW YEARS BACK.

23:40.730 --> 23:43.190
BECAUSE THEY WERE FORCED
TO WORK IN THE STORM.

23:43.200 --> 23:44.830
THAT'S JUST
NOT GIVING A DAMN.

23:44.830 --> 23:47.430
[ MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYS ]

23:47.430 --> 23:52.160
♪♪

23:52.160 --> 23:53.760
BUT YOU GIVE A DAMN.

23:53.760 --> 23:56.360
I MEAN, THE WORK THAT
YOU'RE DOING AT THE BORDER

23:56.360 --> 23:58.830
MAKES A DIFFERENCE,
RIGHT?

23:58.830 --> 24:01.890
I'M JUST ONE MAN.

24:01.900 --> 24:04.560
WELL, IF YOU COULD DO MORE,
WHAT WOULD IT BE?

24:06.600 --> 24:09.490
MORE.
JUST -- JUST MORE.

24:09.500 --> 24:12.130
SET UP THE STATIONS
FOR PEOPLE WHO NEED IT.

24:12.130 --> 24:16.530
ANONYMOUS,
SAFE, CLEAN.

24:16.530 --> 24:17.930
WHAT WOULD IT TAKE
TO GET SOMETHING LIKE THAT

24:17.930 --> 24:19.330
UP AND RUNNING?

24:19.330 --> 24:22.790
VOLUNTEERS
AND A SAFE, CLEAN SPACE

24:22.800 --> 24:25.060
THAT'S NOT VISIBLE
FROM THE STREET.

24:25.060 --> 24:28.530
BUT, UH,
THAT GETS EXPENSIVE.

24:28.530 --> 24:30.090
HM...

24:32.330 --> 24:35.660
SO, I HAVE
A SPACE --

24:35.660 --> 24:38.060
THE FORMER BARRACKS
IN THE BACK OF THE MILL.

24:40.600 --> 24:42.990
IT'S VACANT.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.930
I MEAN, IF YOU CAN GET
THE VOLUNTEERS,

24:44.930 --> 24:47.060
AND I'D PAY
FOR THE SUPPLIES.

24:47.060 --> 24:50.530
WE COULD JUST DO IT THERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:50.530 --> 24:51.690
ARE YOU SERIOUS
RIGHT NOW?

24:53.700 --> 24:57.160
I-I MEAN, 'CAUSE THAT --
THAT COULD WORK.

24:57.160 --> 25:00.390
WE CAN DO, UH, MAYBE
A P.O.P. CLINIC ONCE A WEEK.

25:01.860 --> 25:03.990
FOR NOW.

25:04.000 --> 25:05.260
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

25:05.260 --> 25:10.730
♪♪

25:10.730 --> 25:12.330
VERY.

25:14.060 --> 25:15.030
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:24.130 --> 25:27.390
[ SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS ]

25:27.400 --> 25:33.130
♪♪

25:33.130 --> 25:39.060
♪♪

25:39.060 --> 25:40.160
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

25:43.000 --> 25:44.930
YOU CAN'T HURT ME
AGAIN.

25:44.930 --> 25:51.530
♪♪

25:51.530 --> 25:54.790
YEAH, BLUE MAMA AND I --
WE JUST GOT ON GOOD TERMS,

25:54.800 --> 25:57.660
SO IT'S NOT HAPPENING OVERNIGHT,
TELL YOU THAT MUCH.

25:57.660 --> 25:59.630
IT'S A PROCESS.
YEAH.

25:59.630 --> 26:03.030
I'M STILL NOT THERE
WITH JOIE'S DAD YET.

26:03.030 --> 26:07.790
JUST FOUND IT BEST TO STAY
AS FAR APART AS POSSIBLE.

26:07.800 --> 26:10.660
HE DOESN'T COME AROUND MUCH,
SO IT WORKS.

26:10.660 --> 26:16.130
♪♪

26:16.130 --> 26:18.660
LISTEN, UH...

26:18.660 --> 26:21.460
I JUST WANT TO KEEP IT REAL
WITH YOU.

26:21.460 --> 26:23.730
I DID SOME THINGS IN MY PAST
THAT I HAD TO PAY FOR.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.160
I WAS --
I KNOW.

26:29.400 --> 26:30.560
I RAN
YOUR BACKGROUND.

26:32.460 --> 26:35.190
OLD HABITS DIE HARD
WHEN YOU'RE A PUBLIC DEFENDER

26:35.200 --> 26:38.390
AND DATING
AND HAVE A KID.

26:38.400 --> 26:40.030
I RESPECT THAT.

26:42.860 --> 26:45.260
I READ YOUR FILE.

26:45.260 --> 26:49.190
BUT MY WORK HAS TAUGHT ME
PEOPLE AREN'T THEIR FILES.

26:49.200 --> 26:50.360
YOU'RE CERTAINLY NOT.

26:52.700 --> 26:54.230
AH, THIS PIE
IS SO GOOD.

26:54.230 --> 26:56.390
I FEEL LIKE I'M DOING
SOMETHING WRONG BY EATING IT.

26:56.400 --> 26:57.730
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:57.730 --> 26:58.790
WELL, LET ME
HELP YOU OUT.

26:58.800 --> 26:59.860
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

27:02.060 --> 27:04.460
FEELS GOOD
IN HERE.

27:04.460 --> 27:05.990
HELP YOURSELF
TO WHATEVER.

27:06.000 --> 27:07.860
YES.

27:07.860 --> 27:09.530
WATER'S FINE.

27:09.530 --> 27:11.190
WATER.

27:11.200 --> 27:12.690
SO HEALTHY.

27:17.230 --> 27:18.560
[ REFRIGERATOR DOOR CLOSES ]

27:20.660 --> 27:25.530
♪♪

27:25.530 --> 27:26.730
WHAT'S WRONG?

27:26.730 --> 27:28.990
♪♪

27:29.000 --> 27:31.460
"MICAH WEST,
CLOSE YOUR BIG, LOUD MOUTH,

27:31.460 --> 27:35.260
OR WE WILL FILL IT WITH
YOUR BLOOD AND OUR BULLETS."

27:35.260 --> 27:36.730
-WHAT?
-"KEEP STIRRING UP TROUBLE

27:36.730 --> 27:38.460
IN ST. JO,
AND WE WILL PUT YOU DOWN

27:38.460 --> 27:40.130
LIKE THE FILTHY MUTT
YOU ARE."

27:40.130 --> 27:42.930
OH, MY GOD.

27:42.930 --> 27:44.430
WE NEED TO TAKE THIS
TO THE POLICE.

27:44.430 --> 27:46.030
WHAT ARE THEY
GONNA DO?

27:46.030 --> 27:50.060
♪♪

27:50.060 --> 27:51.660
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

27:51.660 --> 27:57.560
♪♪

28:04.000 --> 28:06.290
I'LL DEAL WITH THIS.
JUST LET ME FIX IT.

28:06.300 --> 28:08.030
HOW DO YOU FIX
A DEATH THREAT?

28:11.630 --> 28:13.160
I'M ON IT.

28:15.700 --> 28:20.360
WHY DOES IT SEEM LIKE I CAN'T
DO ANYTHING RIGHT BY YOU LATELY?

28:20.360 --> 28:21.690
I DON'T KNOW.
I THINK I'M JUST ACCEPTING

28:21.700 --> 28:23.430
THE FACT THAT WE'RE
TWO DIFFERENT PEOPLE

28:23.430 --> 28:25.260
WITH TWO DIFFERENT VIEWS
OF THE WORLD.

28:34.800 --> 28:36.590
[ DRAWER UNLOCKS, OPENS ]

28:45.700 --> 28:47.030
YOU RECEIVED
THE FIRST ONE

28:47.030 --> 28:50.090
A WEEK AFTER YOUR SPEECH
AT THE PRISON RALLY.

28:52.800 --> 28:56.460
AND THIS ONE CAME...

28:56.460 --> 28:57.430
TWO DAYS LATER.

28:59.600 --> 29:02.130
SO I SENT YOU TO PARIS
FOR THE SUMMER

29:02.130 --> 29:04.460
AND HIRED YOU A SECURITY DETAIL
YOU NEVER KNEW ABOUT.

29:04.460 --> 29:05.790
WHAT?

29:05.800 --> 29:07.730
THIS ONE CAME...

29:07.730 --> 29:12.460
THE DAY THAT I TOOK YOU
TO THE AIRPORT TO GO TO PARIS.

29:12.460 --> 29:15.160
THESE CAME
THE DAY AFTER YOU LEFT.

29:15.160 --> 29:16.930
MICAH,
WHAT DO YOU SEE?

29:16.930 --> 29:19.960
LETTERS THREATENING
TO KILL ME.

29:19.960 --> 29:23.490
AND HOW DO YOU FEEL
NOW THAT YOU'VE SEEN THEM?

29:23.500 --> 29:24.860
ANGRY.

29:24.860 --> 29:26.190
WELL, I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO BE ANGRY.

29:28.600 --> 29:32.360
I'M TOO BUSY
BEING AFRAID FOR YOU.

29:32.360 --> 29:34.490
SO IF WE SEE
THE WORLD DIFFERENTLY,

29:36.830 --> 29:39.630
IT'S BECAUSE
I AM COMMITTED

29:39.630 --> 29:42.660
TO DOING WHATEVER I HAVE TO DO
TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

29:44.460 --> 29:47.730
IF THAT MEANS SENDING YOU
TO PARIS FOR THREE MONTHS...

29:47.730 --> 29:49.390
[ DRAWER CLOSES ]

29:49.400 --> 29:51.860
...I'M FINE
WITH THAT.

29:51.860 --> 29:53.930
♪♪

29:53.930 --> 29:57.660
IF THAT MEANS ASKING YOU
TO TRUST ME...

29:58.900 --> 30:01.730
...I'M FINE
WITH THAT.

30:01.730 --> 30:03.090
IF THAT MEANS...

30:03.100 --> 30:08.130
♪♪

30:08.130 --> 30:13.460
♪♪

30:13.460 --> 30:15.060
LET ME PROTECT YOU.

30:15.060 --> 30:20.190
♪♪

30:20.200 --> 30:21.190
IT'S MY JOB.

30:21.200 --> 30:30.090
♪♪

30:33.200 --> 30:36.530
MOM!
HEY!

30:36.530 --> 30:38.460
WHERE'D
YOU GUYS GO?

30:38.460 --> 30:40.190
I TEXTED YOU.

30:40.200 --> 30:42.190
DAD SURPRISED ME
AFTER SCHOOL.

30:42.200 --> 30:45.660
WE WENT TO THE ROLLER RINK,
AND ME AND JOIE GOT ICE CREAM.

30:45.660 --> 30:47.660
I GOT CHOCOLATE MINT.

30:47.660 --> 30:48.790
SUPER GOOD.

30:48.800 --> 30:50.130
JOIE.

30:50.130 --> 30:51.260
WHO IS THAT?

30:51.260 --> 30:52.790
Ralph Angel: NEW FRIEND
HE MET AFTER SCHOOL.

30:52.800 --> 30:55.190
HE WANTED TO DO A LITTLE
PLAY DATE AT THE PLAYGROUND.

30:55.200 --> 30:56.330
I SEE.

30:56.330 --> 30:57.560
HOPE IT DIDN'T RUIN
YOUR APPETITE.

30:57.560 --> 31:00.130
IT WAS ONLY
TWO SCOOPS.

31:00.130 --> 31:02.930
Ralph Angel: ALRIGHT, GO WASH
THAT OUTSIDE OFF YOU, BLUE.

31:02.930 --> 31:04.590
TAKE YOUR BACKPACK
OFF.

31:06.800 --> 31:10.460
[ SIGHS ] I GOT TO TALK
TO YOU ABOUT SOMETHING.

31:10.460 --> 31:11.930
OKAY.

31:14.800 --> 31:18.130
NOVA WROTE ABOUT BLUE
IN HER BOOK.

31:18.130 --> 31:19.730
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

31:19.730 --> 31:21.260
WHAT DID SHE
WRITE ABOUT HIM?

31:23.960 --> 31:25.760
WHAT THE HELL
DID SHE WRITE ABOUT HIM?

31:29.100 --> 31:31.060
THAT I AIN'T
HIS BIOLOGICAL FATHER.

31:31.060 --> 31:35.990
♪♪

31:36.000 --> 31:37.190
WHY WOULD SHE
DO THIS?

31:37.200 --> 31:38.390
[ SIGHS ]
[ SCOFFS ]

31:38.400 --> 31:42.660
♪♪

31:42.660 --> 31:43.790
WHY WOULD SHE --

31:43.800 --> 31:47.490
♪♪

31:47.500 --> 31:50.560
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

31:50.560 --> 31:53.360
I AM SO...

31:53.360 --> 31:55.790
SORRY.

31:55.800 --> 31:58.460
AIN'T YOUR FAULT.

31:58.460 --> 31:59.790
I AIN'T BLAMING YOU.

31:59.800 --> 32:03.230
DID SHE WRITE
ABOUT OUR PAST?

32:03.230 --> 32:06.130
I MEAN...
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

32:06.130 --> 32:08.930
HOW -- HOW CAN SHE GET INTO BLUE
WITHOUT WRITING ABOUT US, TOO?

32:08.930 --> 32:10.660
I AIN'T READ MUCH MORE
AFTER THAT PART.

32:10.660 --> 32:12.190
I...

32:12.200 --> 32:14.330
I COULDN'T.

32:14.330 --> 32:15.660
WHY WOULD SHE DO THIS?

32:15.660 --> 32:17.360
YOU KNOW NOVA.

32:17.360 --> 32:19.260
SHE GONNA DO WHAT SHE WANT,
HOW SHE WANT,

32:19.260 --> 32:21.460
AND IT'S ALWAYS
RIGHT FOR NOVA.

32:21.460 --> 32:25.330
DOES SHE EVEN CONSIDER
OTHER PEOPLE'S FEELINGS?

32:25.330 --> 32:26.660
THIS HURTS YOU.

32:26.660 --> 32:28.960
[ Sighing ]
OH, GOD.

32:28.960 --> 32:30.590
AND IT'S GONNA
HURT BLUE.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.730
NOT LET
THAT HAPPEN.

32:32.730 --> 32:34.930
CAN'T LET
THAT HAPPEN.

32:34.930 --> 32:37.460
I KNOW IT MIGHT TAKE
SOME TIME, PROCESS THIS,

32:37.460 --> 32:41.460
BUT, TIME'S RIGHT...

32:41.460 --> 32:44.660
LET'S SPEAK
TO HIM TOGETHER.

32:44.660 --> 32:46.190
ALRIGHT?

32:48.930 --> 32:50.860
ALRIGHT.

32:50.860 --> 32:52.630
[ DOOR OPENS ]
Violet: THERE HE IS.

32:52.630 --> 32:54.030
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
HE IS GONNA LOVE

32:54.030 --> 32:55.730
THAT I MADE
THIS CHICKEN POT PIE.

32:58.130 --> 33:00.460
[ OMINOUS CHORD STRIKES ]

33:00.460 --> 33:02.130
SO, YOU<i> DO</i>
STILL LIVE HERE.

33:03.860 --> 33:05.630
GOOD TO SEE YOU,
VIOLET.

33:05.630 --> 33:06.790
YOU LOOK GOOD,
BABY.

33:06.800 --> 33:10.590
♪♪

33:10.600 --> 33:11.690
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

33:13.200 --> 33:16.660
WHY -- WHY DON'T YOU
OPEN THE DOOR?

33:16.660 --> 33:17.990
LET ME
COME IN PROPER

33:18.000 --> 33:20.260
SO WE CAN
SET FOR A SPELL,

33:20.260 --> 33:22.630
TALK THINGS OUT.

33:22.630 --> 33:24.390
WE DUE FOR A TALK.

33:24.400 --> 33:25.560
LIKE ADULTS.

33:28.460 --> 33:29.890
NO, YOU NEED
TO LEAVE NOW.

33:32.130 --> 33:35.330
I DONE CAME ALL THIS WAY
TO SEE YOU, VIOLET.

33:36.600 --> 33:38.290
DON'T TURN ME AWAY.

33:38.300 --> 33:39.890
WE ARE GROWN.

33:39.900 --> 33:43.030
WE ARE GROWN PAST
ALL THAT CHILDISH NONSENSE,

33:43.030 --> 33:44.930
AND WE BOTH CHANGED.

33:44.930 --> 33:48.730
SO I'M JUST HERE TO GET BACK
ON THE RIGHT TRACK WITH YOU.

33:48.730 --> 33:50.360
THAT'S ALL.

33:52.330 --> 33:53.990
COME ON, SWEET CAKES.

33:54.000 --> 34:02.890
♪♪

34:02.900 --> 34:11.890
♪♪

34:11.900 --> 34:14.190
I SEE YOU MADE
SOME CHANGES.

34:14.200 --> 34:17.190
STILL FEELS LIKE
MY HOUSE, THOUGH.

34:17.200 --> 34:19.930
SMELLS LIKE
YOU AND YOUR COOKING,

34:19.930 --> 34:22.760
AND I DO MISS BOTH,
I WILL TELL YOU.

34:24.130 --> 34:25.660
BUT I DIDN'T MARRY YOU
FOR YOUR COOKING, NOW.

34:29.000 --> 34:29.890
SO HOW YOU DOING?

34:32.060 --> 34:33.860
VIOLET,
I'M TALKING TO YOU.

34:33.860 --> 34:39.130
♪♪

34:39.130 --> 34:42.060
NOT YOUR HOUSE,
JIMMY.

34:42.060 --> 34:44.930
MY HOUSE.

34:44.930 --> 34:48.130
I SEE YOU GOT YOURSELF
THAT BOY.

34:48.130 --> 34:51.530
YOUR, UH,
NEW HUSBAND.

34:51.530 --> 34:53.060
HOLLYWOOD?

34:53.060 --> 34:55.260
IS THAT IT?

34:55.260 --> 34:56.230
HE AIN'T A BOY.

34:57.400 --> 34:59.590
[ LAUGHS ]

34:59.600 --> 35:02.660
I AIN'T NEVER MET NO MAN
ALLOW HIMSELF TO BE CALLED THAT.

35:03.660 --> 35:06.260
NO, THAT AIN'T
NO MAN.

35:06.260 --> 35:10.460
THAT'S THE NAME OF A BOY
WITH STUPID DREAMS.

35:10.460 --> 35:11.660
I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO TALK ABOUT HIM.

35:11.660 --> 35:13.090
I CAME HERE
TO TALK ABOUT US.

35:14.860 --> 35:17.660
LISTEN, I AM SORRY
HOW WE LEFT THINGS.

35:17.660 --> 35:19.730
I WAS JUST...

35:19.730 --> 35:22.590
A YOUNG, DUMB MAN
BACK THEN.

35:22.600 --> 35:24.590
EVERYBODY MAKES
MISTAKES,

35:24.600 --> 35:27.460
BUT NOT EVERYBODY'S MAN ENOUGH
TO ADMIT TO THEM.

35:27.460 --> 35:31.330
SOME COME TO THEY DIGNITY
LATER IN LIFE.

35:31.330 --> 35:35.190
YOU THE LAST PERSON
WHO CAN EVER TALK ABOUT DIGNITY,

35:35.200 --> 35:37.790
JIMMY DALE.

35:37.800 --> 35:39.060
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

35:39.060 --> 35:41.060
SO THAT'S HOW YOU
GONNA DO ME?

35:41.060 --> 35:42.930
AFTER ALL THIS TIME?

35:42.930 --> 35:45.130
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT.
THERE'S THE DOOR.

35:45.130 --> 35:47.130
USE IT.
[ VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES ]

35:47.130 --> 35:49.030
STILL GOT
THAT SPICE IN YOU.

35:53.600 --> 35:56.260
JIMMY DALE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

35:56.260 --> 35:57.530
HE'S JUST LEAVING.

35:57.530 --> 35:59.630
OH, HEY, NOVA.
GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

36:02.200 --> 36:03.790
EXCUSE ME --
"AGAIN"?

36:05.930 --> 36:08.530
WHAT'S HE
TALKING ABOUT?

36:08.530 --> 36:10.130
I CAN EXPLAIN.

36:10.130 --> 36:13.090
♪♪

36:15.730 --> 36:16.990
I CAN EXPLAIN.

36:17.000 --> 36:18.330
Violet:
WHATEVER YOU DID

36:18.330 --> 36:22.190
TO BRING THIS
TO MY DOORSTEP,

36:22.200 --> 36:23.860
YOU CAN'T
EXPLAIN IT.

36:23.860 --> 36:26.330
WELL, SHE AIN'T GOT
TO EXPLAIN NOTHING.

36:26.330 --> 36:29.330
I'M JUST HERE TO SEE
HOW THE YEARS TREATED YOU,

36:29.330 --> 36:31.590
AND, FROM WHERE
I'M STANDING,

36:31.600 --> 36:33.930
THE YEARS
DONE GOOD BY YOU.

36:33.930 --> 36:34.930
JUST A LITTLE POOCH --

36:34.930 --> 36:37.060
DON'T YOU
GET NEAR HER!!

36:37.060 --> 36:39.690
-GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME!
-GET OUT!

36:39.700 --> 36:41.630
GET OUT! GET OUT!

36:41.630 --> 36:45.090
GO! GET OUT!

36:45.100 --> 36:47.290
YOU WANT TO SHOW YOUR FACE
AT OUR HOUSE MAN,

36:47.300 --> 36:48.760
IS YOU OUT
YOUR DAMN MIND?

36:48.760 --> 36:51.230
I WAS TRYING TO BE NICE TO YOU,
BUT I AIN'T THE ONE, BOY.

36:51.230 --> 36:52.530
I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU.

36:52.530 --> 36:55.960
AAH!
Violet: NO! HOLLYWOOD, NO!

36:55.960 --> 36:56.960
STOP!

36:56.960 --> 36:59.190
YOU'RE GONNA KILL HIM!
[ GRUNTING ]

36:59.200 --> 37:00.260
HOLLYWOOD, STOP!

37:00.260 --> 37:09.190
♪♪

37:09.200 --> 37:11.860
[ Out of breath ] I SEE
WHY YOU HELD ONTO YOUR ANGER

37:11.860 --> 37:13.730
ALL THIS TIME, VIOLET.

37:13.730 --> 37:15.990
'CAUSE I TOOK
SOMETHING FROM YOU

37:16.000 --> 37:17.990
THAT YOU AIN'T NEVER
GONNA GET BACK,

37:18.000 --> 37:20.730
BUT I JUST CAME HERE
TO SAY I WAS SORRY.

37:20.730 --> 37:22.390
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

37:22.400 --> 37:24.190
I AIN'T SORRY AT ALL.

37:24.200 --> 37:26.660
I AIN'T SORRY
ABOUT A DAMN THING.

37:26.660 --> 37:32.790
♪♪

37:32.800 --> 37:35.030
YOU ARE
WHAT YOU ALWAYS WERE --

37:35.030 --> 37:37.690
EARNEST'S
LITTLE SASSY SISTER,

37:37.700 --> 37:40.290
BUT YOU WERE
ONE HOT PIECE OF ASS.

37:40.300 --> 37:41.690
[ HOLLYWOOD GRUNTS ]

37:41.700 --> 37:43.230
I NEVER SHOULD'VE TRIED
TO MAKE YOU A WIFE.

37:43.230 --> 37:44.830
Violet: HE DOESN'T MATTER.
HE DOESN'T MATTER.

37:44.830 --> 37:46.430
HE'S NOT WORTH IT.

37:46.430 --> 37:51.660
♪♪

37:51.660 --> 37:56.730
♪♪

37:56.730 --> 37:58.660
I NEVER MEANT FOR THINGS
TO COME TO THIS.

37:58.660 --> 37:59.990
YEAH,
YOU NEVER DO.

38:02.560 --> 38:04.230
WELL, I'LL START
WITH THE TRUTH.

38:06.830 --> 38:09.360
I DID GO TALK TO JIMMY DALE
FOR MY BOOK.

38:11.360 --> 38:13.190
I THOUGHT IT WAS FOR
A GOOD REASON AT THE TIME.

38:13.200 --> 38:15.360
I WANTED TO GET ALL SIDES
OF THE STORY.

38:18.400 --> 38:22.590
I WAS HOPING TO EXPLORE WHETHER
REDEMPTION WAS POSSIBLE --

38:22.600 --> 38:24.190
EVEN FOR THE WORST OF US,

38:24.200 --> 38:27.360
FOR THOSE WITH
UNFORGIVABLE PASTS --

38:30.000 --> 38:31.590
BUT I REALIZED
AFTER TALKING TO HIM

38:31.600 --> 38:34.790
THAT HE WAS THE SAME PIECE
OF TRASH YOU ALWAYS SAID HE WAS,

38:34.800 --> 38:36.460
AND THAT'S WHY I LEFT
HIS POINT OF VIEW

38:36.460 --> 38:38.860
OUT OF THE BOOK.

38:38.860 --> 38:40.660
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT
VISITING HIM WOULD MAKE HIM

38:40.660 --> 38:44.590
COME STIR UP TROUBLE
IN ST. JO.

38:44.600 --> 38:48.390
ALL I WANTED TO DO
WAS CELEBRATE YOUR TRIUMPH.

38:48.400 --> 38:50.390
EVERYTHING THAT YOU'VE
BEEN THROUGH --

38:50.400 --> 38:53.790
WHAT SO MANY
HAVE BEEN THROUGH.

38:53.800 --> 38:55.130
I DIDN'T FEEL LIKE
I COULD DO THAT

38:55.130 --> 38:57.060
IF I LEAVE
HALF THE STORY OUT.

39:00.730 --> 39:03.990
MY INTENTION
WASN'T TO HURT ANYONE.

39:04.000 --> 39:06.990
♪♪

39:07.000 --> 39:10.130
YOU HAVE DONE SOME THINGS
IN YOUR DAY, CHILD.

39:10.130 --> 39:15.260
♪♪

39:15.260 --> 39:16.460
BUT THIS...

39:16.460 --> 39:20.060
♪♪

39:20.060 --> 39:21.730
...YOUR DADDY
WOULD BE ASHAMED.

39:21.730 --> 39:24.590
♪♪

39:24.600 --> 39:28.060
YOUR MAMA --

39:28.060 --> 39:30.790
YOUR MAMA WOULD DO
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO.

39:30.800 --> 39:33.730
♪♪

39:33.730 --> 39:36.460
YOU NEED
TO LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

39:36.460 --> 39:38.690
I DIDN'T TELL JIMMY --
STOP IT.

39:38.700 --> 39:43.790
♪♪

39:43.800 --> 39:47.130
I DON'T WANT
TO LOOK AT YOU.

39:47.130 --> 39:48.660
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO YOU.

39:51.460 --> 39:54.730
NOT RIGHT NOW,
NOT TOMORROW.

39:54.730 --> 39:57.990
WAY I'M FEELING,
EVEN TEN YEARS

39:58.000 --> 40:00.330
CAN'T PUT ENOUGH DISTANCE
BETWEEN US.

40:00.330 --> 40:04.130
AUNT VI --
DON'T KNOCK AT MY DOORSTEP.

40:04.130 --> 40:06.590
DON'T BRING NO FLOWERS
TO MY GRAVE.

40:06.600 --> 40:09.430
I DON'T NEED YOU...

40:12.530 --> 40:16.260
...DISTURBING ANY MORE
OF MY PEACE.

40:16.260 --> 40:17.860
THIS IS
THE LAST TIME

40:17.860 --> 40:23.260
I LET YOU
IN THIS HOUSE,

40:23.260 --> 40:24.790
NOVA BORDELON.

40:24.800 --> 40:33.790
♪♪

40:33.800 --> 40:42.730
♪♪

